in Los Angeles.

98
00:05:37,710 --> 00:05:38,861
First he spends half the article

99
00:05:38,861 --> 00:05:42,100
praising China’s response to the coronavirus,

100
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:45,680
claiming that its response saved the rest
of the world,

101
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:49,580
and repeating how the World Health Organization
is praising China.

102
00:05:49,580 --> 00:05:52,300
This is exactly the type of propaganda spin

103
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:54,950
we talked about in our previous segment.

104
00:05:54,950 --> 00:05:57,530
But here’s the key paragraph.

105
00:05:57,530 --> 00:05:58,870
The Chinese diplomat brings up

106
00:05:58,870 --> 00:06:02,880
“disturbing reports from around the world
about discrimination

107
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:06,169
and stigmatization of the Chinese community.”

108
00:06:06,169 --> 00:06:08,590
What kind of discrimination?

109
00:06:08,590 --> 00:06:11,940
Xenophobia on social media, attacks on Chinese
people,

110
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:15,200
and discrimination against Chinese doctors.

111
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:18,980
Then in the very next sentence, he says,

112
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:23,230
“And despite its unparalleled response to
the crisis,

113
00:06:23,230 --> 00:06:26,389
the Chinese government has been attacked by
some people

114
00:06:26,389 --> 00:06:28,960
out of ideological prejudice.”

115
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:31,060
In three sentences,

116
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:34,830
this Chinese diplomat equates criticism of
the Chinese government

117
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:39,230
