Chinese people.

118
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:42,680
He’s saying they’re the same thing.

119
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,390
That’s the trick.

120
00:06:44,390 --> 00:06:47,600
They’re taking individual cases of racism,

121
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:51,940
and mixing them with targeted actions against
the Chinese government

122
00:06:51,940 --> 00:06:56,210
and targeted criticisms of the Chinese regime.

123
00:06:56,210 --> 00:07:01,520
And state-run media are spinning it as “the
West is racist against China.”

124
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:06,730
Yes, that’s the trick and people are falling
for it.

125
00:07:06,730 --> 00:07:10,860
In fact, Chinese state-run media have even
gone so far as to say

126
00:07:10,860 --> 00:07:13,960
racism is a worse enemy than the epidemic.

127
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:14,980
Oh right.

128
00:07:14,980 --> 00:07:20,370
It’s *racism* that’s killed 6,000 people
in the past two months.

129
00:07:20,370 --> 00:07:22,410
In February, Chinese state-run media

130
00:07:22,410 --> 00:07:25,560
had criticized the US for implementing a travel
ban

131
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:28,290
on people who had recently been inside China.

132
00:07:28,290 --> 00:07:32,380
And then in March, Chinese state-run media
upped their game:

133
00:07:32,380 --> 00:07:37,870
claiming it’s racist to even say the coronavirus
originated in China.

134
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:39,300
This Global Times article says

135
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:44,120
“Some American officials, including Secretary
of State Mike Pompeo,

136
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:49,090
are using ‘Wuhan virus’ which is considered
a racist term.”

137
00:07:49,090 --> 00:07:55,449
So even though the first cases of the coronavirus
were in Wuhan, China...

138
00:07:55,449 --> 00:07:58,650
it’s racist to say that?

139
00:07:58,650 --> 00:07:59,650
Yes.

140
00:07:59,650 --> 00:08:01,639
Apparently it is.

141
00:08:01,639 --> 00:08:03,850
Because starting in late February,

142
00:08:03,850 --> 00:08:07,210
Chinese state media began spinning a new narrative:

143
00:08:07,210 --> 00:08:10,610
the idea that the coronavirus “may not originate
in China.”

144
00:08:10,610 --> 00:08:14,400
Yes, the origin “still hangs in the air.”

145
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,730
And soon, Chinese social media sites began

146
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:22,010
“pushing the idea that the virus really
originated in the United States.”

147
00:08:22,010 --> 00:08:26,230
And then, the Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesperson
tweeted that,

148
00:08:26,230 --> 00:08:31,180
“It might be [the] US army who brought the
epidemic to Wuhan.”

149
00:08:31,180 --> 00:08:34,789
Now, at first glance, this seems crazy.

150
00:08:34,789 --> 00:08:37,139
But the more they push that idea,

151
00:08:37,139 --> 00:08:39,300
the more people will actually start to question

152
00:08:39,300 --> 00:08:42,070
whether it really did start in China,

153
00:08:42,070 --> 00:08:47,079
especially when you can’t say it did without
being called racist.

154
00:08:47,079 --> 00:08:49,220
The good news is that the US government

155
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:52,100
is not letting them get away with it.

156
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:55,449
Last week, the State Department summoned the
Chinese Ambassador

157
00:08:55,449 --> 00:08:58,790
over the Foreign Ministry spokesperson’s
tweets.

158
00:08:58,790 --> 00:09:02,569
And Secretary of State Mike Pompeo condemned
China’s efforts

159
00:09:02,569 --> 00:09:05,490
to shift the coronavirus blame on the US,

160
00:09:05,490 --> 00:09:08,240
in a phone call with a communist party official.

161
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:11,670
But that hasn’t stopped the Chinese government
from pushing the idea

162
00:09:11,670 --> 00:09:14,730
